==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deambulatory
<hw>De*am"bu*la*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>deambulator</ets> a traveler.]</ety> <def>Going about from place to
place; wandering; of or pertaining to a deambulatory.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Deambulatory</xex> actors.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Bp. Morton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deambulatory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Deambulatory
<hw>De*am"bu*la*to*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deambulatorium</ets>.]</ety> <def>A covered place in which to walk;
an ambulatory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dean</ent>⟦br⟧
